IT WAS a bloody weekend on the country s roads, as 25 people were killed in several accidents. Four people were killed when a truck and a minibus taxi collided on the N1 near Brandfort on Saturday night. Patients were found strewn across the scene of the accident when paramedics arrived. Sadly, two people found in the taxi and two who were believed to have been ejected had succumbed to their injuries, ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing said.Five people died in a head-on collision between a minibus taxi and an SUV on the N2 road between Qumbu and Tsolo. The accident claimed the lives of two children and a third child was admitted to a local hospital. Limpopo police said they were investigating a case of culpable homicide following the death of six people during a collision between two vehicles near Mookgopong. Bodasing said a man believed to be in his 20s died after losing control of his vehicle in Cato Ridge. Another person died when two vehicles collided on the N1 at the Maraisburg offramp.zodidim@thenewage.co.za-Zodidi Mhlana